  DEFAULT locale = Marathi.
  This file is what Android falls back to when the device locale doesn't match
  any values-<lang>/ bucket (e.g. en_VI, en_US, hi_IN without a hi bucket).
  The app is Marathi-first, so we keep Marathi here as the safe fallback.

  English-language users see values-en/strings.xml when they pick "English" in
  Settings (AppCompatDelegate.setApplicationLocales("en")).

  Convention: the `settings_*` keys are intentionally kept in English across
  all locales so farmers can always find the language toggle even if they have
  switched to a language they cannot read.
-->
